incident_updates.body:

scheduled_maintenances.name: Scheduled Zoom Software Quarterly Lifecycle Update (11/2/2024)

incident_updates.body:
As a reminder roughly 30 days ahead of the upcoming enforcement, Zoom will be enforcing a new global minimum version for all our Zoom clients and plugins this November 2nd. This affects the following products:
- Zoom app for meetings (Windows, macOS, Linux, iOS, Android, Blackberry, and Intune)
- Zoom Rooms and Controllers
- Zoom Phone Appliances
- VDI Client and Plugin
- Virtual Room Connector
- Meetings Connector
- Recording Connector
- Meeting SDK (Native and web)
- Video SDK (Native and web)
- Zoom Contact Center SDK (Native)
- Zoom Node (including Meeting Connector ZC and MMR)
- Zoom Phone Local Survivability (ZPLS) module

For more information, such as specific versions we are enforcing, refer to the Zoom Software Quarterly Lifecycle Policy support article: https://support.zoom.com/hc/en/article?id=zm_kb&sysparm_article=KB0061130 

To assist with checking the client versions on your account, refer to the Dashboard support article: https://support.zoom.com/hc/en/article?id=zm_kb&sysparm_article=KB0062208#h_13ce9a73-91e5-4df6-9cb5-c815b1605cf5

Zoom will be enforcing a new minimum version of all our Zoom clients and plugins, roughly 90 days from now on November 2, 2024. This affects the following products: 

- Zoom app for meetings (Windows, macOS, Linux, iOS, Android, Blackberry, and Intune)
- Zoom Rooms (including Zoom Room Controllers and companion whiteboards) 
- Zoom Phone Appliances
- VDI Client and Plugin
- Virtual Room Connector
- Meetings Connector
- Recording Connector
- Meetings SDK (Native and Web)
- Video SDK (Native and Web)
- Zoom Contact Center SDK (Native)
- Zoom Node (including Meeting Connector ZC and MMR)
- Zoom Phone Local Survivability (ZPLS) module

Please ensure your devices are updated to the latest version. 

For more information, such as specific versions we are enforcing, refer to the Zoom Software Quarterly Lifecycle Policy support article: https://support.zoom.com/hc/en/article?id=zm_kb&sysparm_article=KB0061130 

To assist with checking the client versions on your account, refer to the Dashboard support article: https://support.zoom.com/hc/en/article?id=zm_kb&sysparm_article=KB0062208#h_13ce9a73-91e5-4df6-9cb5-c815b1605cf5
